# Hexalyte UX Standards

When changing dashboard pages, keep these patterns. Do not add onboarding panels, coach strips, or plan docs unless explicitly requested.

## Clicks & navigation

- Prefer **inline modals** over `router.push` to a wrapper route for create/edit flows.
- Support **URL deep links**: `?action=add|new`, `?id=`, `?q=` to open forms, detail modals, or prefill search.
- **Primary column clickable** (ticket #, invoice #, customer name) → detail modal; optional double-click → edit.
- **Stat cards / chips** filter lists in one click; avoid nested dropdown-only filters when chips work.

## Search & tables

- **One** `ToolbarSearch` per page toolbar — never duplicate with `ClientSideTable` `searchableColumns`.
- Pass `searchableColumns={[]}` and `showFilter={false}` when filters live in the page toolbar.
- Persist list filters in `sessionStorage` when users commonly refresh (inventory, repairs).

## Modals & keyboard

- **Esc** closes modals (`keydown` listener, remove on unmount).
- Reuse `FilterDropdown` and `ToolbarSearch` from `@/components/ui/`.
- Mobile: branch switcher and toolbars must work without `hidden sm:` blocking core actions.

## Scope

- UX only — do not change business logic, API contracts, or break backward-compatible routes.
- No new banners/panels for “tips” or setup guides.
